definition: to take in and send out (in large quantities)
to spit/to send out (silk from a silkworm, bolls from cotton flowers etc)/to say/to pour out (one's grievances)
to hum and haw (idiom); to mumble as if hiding sth/to speak and break off, then start again/to hold sth back

sentences.english: Event throughput is bound by the server speed.
sentences.chinese: 事件吞吐量受服務器的速度限制。

sentences.english: He hesitated and added, the muscles of his face contracting whitely.
sentences.chinese: 他一臉的肌肉在皺縮發白，一面吞吞吐吐地接下去說。

sentences.english: Reducing variability frequently incurs a drop in latency and throughput performance.
sentences.chinese: 減少易變性通常會增加延遲時間和降低吞吐量性能。

sentences.english: Simulation results show that the presented scheme can efficiently improve network throughputs.
sentences.chinese: 仿真結果表明，所提方案可以有效地提高網絡吞吐量。

sentences.chinese: 最大流最小割定理決定了網絡的最大吞吐量。

sentences.english: Large windows are necessary for decent throughput on high-latency links.

sentences.english: We'd like to designate London as the loading port, for it has larger accommodation capacity.

sentences.chinese: 那是什麼病痛呀？這人似乎決意吞吞吐吐。

sentences.english: He began to hem when talking about where he was that night.
sentences.chinese: 一談到那天夜裏他在哪兒，他就開始吞吞吐吐起來。

sentences.english: Call him, he said, speak hesitatingly or continue to make friends.
sentences.chinese: 給他打電話，他吞吞吐吐說不合適，還是繼續做朋友。

sentences.english: Concurrency and throughput also have to do with when you release the locks.
